The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision task, and specifically focuses on the use of deep learning methods. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes methods for training and fine-tuning the model, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of multiple datasets and cross-dataset evaluation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia), while the application of the model to visual surveillance implies a potential fit with cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of unsupervised fine-tuning may also relate to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
